1
00:00:35,076 --> 00:00:39,748
Mikoy loves dramas,
and even I'm starting to like it too.

2
00:00:39,831 --> 00:00:44,461
But what I don't like, is they
always incorporate a third-party.

3
00:00:46,421 --> 00:00:49,716
Not now, I'm busy with the bakery.

4
00:00:49,799 --> 00:00:51,050
This won't take long, I promise.

5
00:00:51,134 --> 00:00:52,844
Angelito, I want to court Sofie.

6
00:00:52,927 --> 00:00:54,637
Can you help me?

7
00:01:30,882 --> 00:01:36,095
Report to me once you found them.

8
00:02:00,787 --> 00:02:02,080
<i>Oh, my goodness!</i>

9
00:02:02,163 --> 00:02:03,373
<i>Oh, my goodness, yes!</i>

10
00:02:03,456 --> 00:02:06,167
<i>Alex burned her eggs!</i>

11
00:02:06,251 --> 00:02:07,669
<i>Oh, my goodness!</i>

12
00:02:07,752 --> 00:02:09,003
<i>Oh, my goodness, yes!</i>

13
00:02:09,087 --> 00:02:11,923
<i>Alex burned her eggs!</i>

14
00:02:13,633 --> 00:02:16,469
<i>She's fearless against criminals</i>

15
00:02:16,553 --> 00:02:19,139
<i>But she's no match for an egg</i>

16
00:02:19,222 --> 00:02:22,100
<i>I wonder who's on Alex's mind?</i>

17
00:02:22,183 --> 00:02:24,519
<i>I wonder who's in Alex's heart?</i>

18
00:02:24,602 --> 00:02:28,439
<i>I know who Alex likes</i>

19
00:02:29,315 --> 00:02:31,067
You talk too much.

20
00:02:37,115 --> 00:02:38,700
Hey!

21
00:02:39,492 --> 00:02:40,869
Wait.

22
00:02:40,952 --> 00:02:44,122
Is this the radioactive bomb?

23
00:02:44,205 --> 00:02:47,584
Or maybe a weapon of mass destruction?

24
00:02:49,711 --> 00:02:51,087
Okay, sorry.

25
00:02:52,505 --> 00:02:53,548
What?

26
00:02:53,631 --> 00:02:54,591
Did you cook this?

27
00:02:58,219 --> 00:03:01,848
You know, I'm not forcing you to eat it.
Don't eat it, then. I'll eat it myself.

28
00:03:01,931 --> 00:03:05,393
Look at you, getting offended already.
Of course we're going to try it.

29
00:03:13,818 --> 00:03:17,822
PINAGPALA - SPECIAL BAKESHOP

30
00:03:17,906 --> 00:03:18,740
Sofie.

31
00:03:19,991 --> 00:03:21,326
What are you looking at?

32
00:03:22,744 --> 00:03:24,162
Nothing.

33
00:03:25,538 --> 00:03:27,165
So you're a morning person too, huh?

34
00:03:27,248 --> 00:03:30,251
No, I just came here early.

35
00:03:30,960 --> 00:03:32,170
Where's Luisa?

36
00:03:32,253 --> 00:03:33,713
Aren't you staying at the same hotel?

37
00:03:33,796 --> 00:03:34,881
She said she'll follow later.

38
00:03:35,548 --> 00:03:36,925
Are you staying nearby?

39
00:03:37,967 --> 00:03:41,429
Yes. Actually, it's near the exit.

40
00:03:41,971 --> 00:03:43,473
Just go straight and turn right.

41
00:03:43,556 --> 00:03:45,475
- That's it.
- I see…

42
00:03:46,100 --> 00:03:47,185
Want to go for a run?

43
00:03:50,230 --> 00:03:55,360
Oh, sorry. I'm just not really
in the mood to run right now.

44
00:03:55,443 --> 00:03:57,820
Besides, I told Mama Tess that

45
00:03:57,904 --> 00:03:59,656
I'd help her with the cooking.

46
00:04:00,240 --> 00:04:02,158
I actually have something cooking there.

47
00:04:02,951 --> 00:04:04,077
Maybe next time.

48
00:04:04,744 --> 00:04:06,120
All right, next time.

49
00:04:06,204 --> 00:04:07,747
- You said it.
- Mmm…

50
00:04:07,830 --> 00:04:08,998
I'll hold you to that.

51
00:04:13,336 --> 00:04:15,255
You know, you two…

52
00:04:15,338 --> 00:04:17,340
It's like you got a free honeymoon, huh?

53
00:04:18,383 --> 00:04:21,636
It's like you're just on
a staycation here, right?

54
00:04:22,971 --> 00:04:24,722
You single people, honestly.

55
00:04:24,806 --> 00:04:28,685
The moment you see some sweetness,
you immediately get allergic to it.

56
00:04:28,768 --> 00:04:30,728
Just let Chiara and me enjoy this.

57
00:04:30,812 --> 00:04:31,646
You know,

58
00:04:32,397 --> 00:04:35,441
we got exhausted working
our bones off in Hong Kong.

59
00:04:35,525 --> 00:04:36,943
Why is this so hard?

60
00:04:37,026 --> 00:04:39,570
To be fair, that was your decision.

61
00:04:39,654 --> 00:04:42,699
Who told you to run away
and go to Hong Kong?

62
00:04:43,283 --> 00:04:45,535
All right, it was our fault.

63
00:04:45,618 --> 00:04:47,412
Come on, I just wanted to share

64
00:04:47,495 --> 00:04:48,955
my realizations from that trip.

65
00:04:49,038 --> 00:04:50,873
- All right then, share them.
- Never mind.

66
00:04:50,957 --> 00:04:52,333
- Come on, go ahead!
- No way!

67
00:04:52,417 --> 00:04:54,127
- Come on, come on.
- Okay, fine.

68
00:04:54,210 --> 00:04:57,380
Of course, our work
at the restaurant was exhausting too.

69
00:04:57,463 --> 00:04:59,299
- See? That's why.
- We'd wake up early,

70
00:04:59,382 --> 00:05:00,550
then go to the market.

71
00:05:00,633 --> 00:05:04,137
We'd carry supplies around
and prepare the ingredients.

72
00:05:04,220 --> 00:05:05,221
It was hard.

73
00:05:05,305 --> 00:05:07,140
Yes, that really was hard!

74
00:05:07,223 --> 00:05:10,476
That's why, you know, part of me
actually missed being a COO.

75
00:05:10,560 --> 00:05:12,687
Just sitting in an air-conditioned office.

76
00:05:12,770 --> 00:05:14,731
- Giving people orders.
- What a life!

77
00:05:14,814 --> 00:05:17,567
Yes, instead of doing manual labor, right?

78
00:05:20,486 --> 00:05:24,157
But their job is to make sure
that people in the company have jobs.

79
00:05:24,866 --> 00:05:26,534
I know that.

80
00:05:27,035 --> 00:05:28,745
And what I'm sharing
isn't meant to compare

81
00:05:28,828 --> 00:05:30,038
which job is harder.

82
00:05:30,121 --> 00:05:32,582
My point is, at the end of the day,

83
00:05:32,665 --> 00:05:35,543
there's also satisfaction
in restaurant work.

84
00:05:35,626 --> 00:05:37,003
In manual labor.

85
00:05:37,503 --> 00:05:40,923
Because there,
everyone listens and everyone helps.

86
00:05:41,007 --> 00:05:44,260
And you create something
with your hands, right?

87
00:05:44,343 --> 00:05:45,553
That's amazing.

88
00:05:45,636 --> 00:05:48,806
Then you see how happy people are
eating the food you cooked.

89
00:05:48,890 --> 00:05:51,934
They appreciate it,
and that feels really good.

90
00:05:52,018 --> 00:05:54,604
Wow, these eggs are delicious!

91
00:05:54,687 --> 00:05:56,898
You want some? Fine, I'll eat them all.

92
00:05:56,981 --> 00:05:59,150
Amazing!
I absolutely love the crispy bits!

93
00:05:59,233 --> 00:06:01,235
<i>No, they're completely burnt,</i>

94
00:06:01,319 --> 00:06:03,446
<i>Crunching it down</i>

95
00:06:03,529 --> 00:06:05,531
<i>Crunch, crunch, so delicious!</i>

96
00:06:05,615 --> 00:06:07,200
<i>That's right, bro!</i>

97
00:06:07,283 --> 00:06:08,326
Okay, bro!

98
00:06:08,409 --> 00:06:09,535
- See that!
- Okay!

99
00:06:09,619 --> 00:06:11,537
- That's how it is!
- There you go!

100
00:06:11,621 --> 00:06:13,081
So if I had to choose,

101
00:06:13,164 --> 00:06:15,249
I'd really prefer a job like that.

102
00:06:15,333 --> 00:06:16,542
One that's not in an office.

103
00:06:16,626 --> 00:06:18,544
Because when you're in an office,

104
00:06:18,628 --> 00:06:21,380
you rarely get to see
the people you're making happy.

105
00:06:21,964 --> 00:06:23,341
And sooner or later,

106
00:06:23,841 --> 00:06:27,261
that sense of fulfillment
starts to fade from your heart, right?

107
00:06:30,973 --> 00:06:34,352
But I'd rather be sad in a huge mansion,

108
00:06:34,435 --> 00:06:35,645
wearing my Rolex.

109
00:06:35,728 --> 00:06:36,604
And then,

110
00:06:37,188 --> 00:06:38,022
I'd have lots of money.

111
00:06:38,106 --> 00:06:40,942
It's hard being broke.
You suddenly find yourself crying,

112
00:06:41,025 --> 00:06:42,360
when you have no money.

113
00:06:49,534 --> 00:06:50,576
So what now?

114
00:06:51,119 --> 00:06:53,746
Looks like this is hopeless.

115
00:06:55,081 --> 00:06:56,249
Maybe I should just move on.

116
00:06:56,332 --> 00:06:57,333
You could.

117
00:06:57,416 --> 00:06:58,960
Wow, really?

118
00:06:59,043 --> 00:07:00,878
Not even a few words of encouragement?

119
00:07:00,962 --> 00:07:04,173
So that's what you wanted to hear.
You should've said so right away.

120
00:07:04,757 --> 00:07:08,678
Instead of acting all sad over there,
like you're ready to give up on Sofie.

121
00:07:08,761 --> 00:07:10,763
Of course I'll support you.

122
00:07:11,264 --> 00:07:12,849
But if

123
00:07:12,932 --> 00:07:15,768
you're not even sure about Sofie yet,

124
00:07:17,395 --> 00:07:19,480
then maybe it's better
if you just give up.

125
00:07:20,273 --> 00:07:21,274
You have a point.

126
00:07:22,525 --> 00:07:24,444
But how about this? Favor.

127
00:07:25,153 --> 00:07:28,614
Maybe you can help me find out
Sofie's favorites, like her

128
00:07:28,698 --> 00:07:30,783
favorite color, favorite food.

129
00:07:30,867 --> 00:07:32,910
Anything that could help me court her.

130
00:07:34,954 --> 00:07:36,456
All right, I'll do it for you.

131
00:07:36,539 --> 00:07:39,208
You really love me.

132
00:07:39,917 --> 00:07:40,960
Give me a hug.

133
00:07:43,463 --> 00:07:45,631
Hey, wait. Is that a helicopter?

134
00:07:46,299 --> 00:07:48,050
Looks like one of you escaped.

135
00:07:49,260 --> 00:07:51,053
What? I'm heading out first.

136
00:07:51,137 --> 00:07:52,096
Hey!

137
00:07:52,805 --> 00:07:55,558
- Go ahead.
- You might be with…

138
00:07:55,641 --> 00:07:58,978
PINAGPALA
SPECIAL BAKESHOP

139
00:08:14,952 --> 00:08:15,953
Hello?

140
00:08:17,330 --> 00:08:18,664
How are you doing?

141
00:08:19,165 --> 00:08:21,709
How's our houdini couple there?

142
00:08:21,792 --> 00:08:23,294
Did they do another new stunt?

143
00:08:23,377 --> 00:08:25,046
Surprisingly none.

144
00:08:26,047 --> 00:08:28,382
They're just making
the safehouse their staycation.

145
00:08:28,466 --> 00:08:29,675
But nothing alarming.

146
00:08:29,759 --> 00:08:33,596
And Cocoy is just monitoring
the money flow of the Vertex.

147
00:08:43,231 --> 00:08:44,190
How about you, Bok?

148
00:08:45,733 --> 00:08:47,026
Are you okay?

149
00:08:48,778 --> 00:08:51,489
Aside from cooking, I haven't really
faced any other challenges.

150
00:08:54,534 --> 00:08:57,828
So you've already shown them
your cooking skills.

151
00:08:58,538 --> 00:09:00,831
Sianong, just get to the point.
Why did you call?

152
00:09:00,915 --> 00:09:02,416
Is there a problem at the agency?

153
00:09:02,500 --> 00:09:03,543
Here?

154
00:09:04,210 --> 00:09:05,253
No.

155
00:09:05,336 --> 00:09:07,713
Everything's fine here, okay?

156
00:09:07,797 --> 00:09:11,300
I just wanted to remind you
that you need to send an update.

157
00:09:11,384 --> 00:09:14,971
ASAP, because Senator Quintin
will be briefing

158
00:09:15,054 --> 00:09:16,472
the President.

159
00:09:17,223 --> 00:09:19,016
All right, I'll send it once I'm done.

160
00:09:19,100 --> 00:09:20,601
Agent Alex, we have a problem!

161
00:09:22,144 --> 00:09:23,229
What?

162
00:09:25,565 --> 00:09:27,149
What's the problem? Is it the enemy?

163
00:09:27,233 --> 00:09:28,651
- Take cover! Take cover!
- No.

164
00:09:29,235 --> 00:09:30,319
There's no water!

165
00:09:31,153 --> 00:09:32,655
What? That's it?

166
00:09:32,738 --> 00:09:33,823
What do you mean, that's it?

167
00:09:33,906 --> 00:09:36,284
How am I supposed to finish
washing these dishes?

168
00:09:36,367 --> 00:09:38,119
I can go outside and look for
a place to buy water.

169
00:09:39,787 --> 00:09:40,788
No one is leaving.

170
00:09:40,871 --> 00:09:42,832
This place is in a secluded area.

171
00:09:42,915 --> 00:09:44,834
If it's not an ice cream vendor
who spots you,

172
00:09:44,917 --> 00:09:46,502
it'll be a taho vendor.

173
00:09:46,586 --> 00:09:47,420
What's our game plan?

174
00:09:47,503 --> 00:09:50,965
We can't be without water.
I haven't even showered. I stink already!

175
00:09:51,048 --> 00:09:52,466
And I also need to freshen up.

176
00:09:53,926 --> 00:09:54,760
What's that?

177
00:09:57,513 --> 00:09:59,056
That can only mean one thing.

178
00:09:59,682 --> 00:10:02,184
There's movement in their crypto wallet.

179
00:10:10,860 --> 00:10:12,903
See?! I knew it.

180
00:10:12,987 --> 00:10:15,114
They're using Vertex

181
00:10:15,698 --> 00:10:17,908
to move funds into crypto.

182
00:10:18,993 --> 00:10:20,411
Looks like they routed it through a bank.

183
00:10:21,037 --> 00:10:22,622
How did they manage that?

184
00:10:22,705 --> 00:10:24,290
Shouldn't that have been flagged?

185
00:10:24,373 --> 00:10:26,417
Fifty million pesos?

186
00:10:26,500 --> 00:10:29,337
Not if it's a corporate account
under a legitimate business,

187
00:10:29,420 --> 00:10:30,546
which is Vertex.

188
00:10:30,630 --> 00:10:32,798
They're making it look like
operational expenses,

189
00:10:32,882 --> 00:10:35,968
or business expenses through
multiple transactions.

190
00:10:37,345 --> 00:10:40,306
It's only ordinary people
who get scrutinized by banks here.

191
00:10:42,433 --> 00:10:43,851
That's not all. Look at this.

192
00:10:44,852 --> 00:10:49,065
They're using crypto to transfer
the same amount.

193
00:10:49,148 --> 00:10:51,901
I checked the satellite mapping,

194
00:10:51,984 --> 00:10:55,279
and it's an isolated area in Tanay.

195
00:11:00,951 --> 00:11:03,371
It's possible that this is
the new operational site

196
00:11:03,454 --> 00:11:05,581
of La Morte Bianca in the Philippines.

197
00:11:06,290 --> 00:11:07,708
You're right, Cocoy.

198
00:11:08,292 --> 00:11:10,419
I'm sure their place will
be heavily guarded.

199
00:11:10,503 --> 00:11:13,923
Self-contained and
almost impossible to infiltrate.

200
00:11:14,507 --> 00:11:16,967
Like a mafia village in Prague and Sicily.

201
00:11:18,052 --> 00:11:19,553
Do you think
they're still looking for the bomb?

202
00:11:20,137 --> 00:11:21,472
Or have they already found it?

203
00:11:22,098 --> 00:11:24,183
Well, that's the question
we need answered.

204
00:11:24,266 --> 00:11:26,602
Because if they already have the bomb,

205
00:11:27,603 --> 00:11:30,689
it means catastrophe is near.

206
00:11:31,399 --> 00:11:32,817
And if they don't,

207
00:11:33,609 --> 00:11:36,278
then we still have time to stop them.

208
00:11:48,958 --> 00:11:50,459
Mr. President.

209
00:12:01,887 --> 00:12:03,389
And it did not pass through

210
00:12:03,472 --> 00:12:05,975
standard banking channels.

211
00:12:19,572 --> 00:12:23,617
And she used Vertex,
owned by the Valtrovis,

212
00:12:23,701 --> 00:12:24,869
as a front.

213
00:12:24,952 --> 00:12:28,581
To convert cryptocurrency
into Philippine pesos.

214
00:12:33,294 --> 00:12:35,087
They're the ones
we've been watching for years.

215
00:12:47,391 --> 00:12:48,976
The Concordat.

216
00:12:49,685 --> 00:12:53,314
Their goal is to establish
an administration here in the Philippines,

217
00:12:53,397 --> 00:12:56,358
and spread their terror from here.

218
00:13:15,169 --> 00:13:18,797
In fact, they immediately found the site

219
00:13:18,881 --> 00:13:21,884
that Isabella purchased
as their stronghold.

220
00:13:23,385 --> 00:13:25,429
Impressive, Senator Quintin.

221
00:13:25,930 --> 00:13:27,431
Even your barong is impressive!

222
00:13:30,643 --> 00:13:32,478
You could run for higher office.

223
00:13:33,604 --> 00:13:34,939
Oh, Mr. President.

224
00:13:35,022 --> 00:13:38,526
I still have to
eat a lot of rice and chips.

225
00:13:38,609 --> 00:13:42,655
Although, I don't like
chips because I'm allergic to that.

226
00:13:52,289 --> 00:13:53,374
That was a nuclear bomb!

227
00:14:08,222 --> 00:14:09,348
There.

228
00:14:09,848 --> 00:14:11,767
- Bechay, get this.
- Here, thank you very much.

229
00:14:11,850 --> 00:14:13,102
Come back, okay?

230
00:14:13,185 --> 00:14:15,145
Promise?

231
00:14:16,480 --> 00:14:18,482
Just a typical Angelito…

232
00:14:20,860 --> 00:14:24,446
- Come here, look at them.
- Oh, my. Look at this.

233
00:14:25,906 --> 00:14:27,575
What do you think? What if…

234
00:14:27,658 --> 00:14:31,704
there comes a chance where
Angelito has to choose.

235
00:14:32,204 --> 00:14:34,415
Who do you think he would choose?

236
00:14:35,249 --> 00:14:36,667
They're both kind.

237
00:14:36,750 --> 00:14:37,877
They're both beautiful too.

238
00:14:40,337 --> 00:14:41,505
True that.

239
00:14:42,006 --> 00:14:43,799
But if you ask me?

240
00:14:48,262 --> 00:14:50,556
I'm Team Luisa Mae, Team AngeLu.

241
00:14:51,432 --> 00:14:52,308
Because look,

242
00:14:52,391 --> 00:14:56,103
Luisa Mae seems good with people,

243
00:14:56,186 --> 00:14:57,980
she adjusts to others.

244
00:14:58,063 --> 00:14:59,440
And with Sofie…

245
00:15:00,024 --> 00:15:02,234
She always has to be the one in control.

246
00:15:02,318 --> 00:15:04,737
That's not really okay
all the time, right?

247
00:15:05,404 --> 00:15:07,573
She's just a kid!

248
00:15:07,656 --> 00:15:09,742
She takes after her father!

249
00:15:10,534 --> 00:15:11,785
But me, you know?

250
00:15:11,869 --> 00:15:13,913
If you ask me?

251
00:15:13,996 --> 00:15:15,998
I'm Team SofieLito.

252
00:15:17,333 --> 00:15:18,751
Because of vibes.

253
00:15:18,834 --> 00:15:20,419
Vibes? What vibes?

254
00:15:20,920 --> 00:15:22,671
Just vibes, that's what it is.

255
00:15:22,755 --> 00:15:26,300
That only a mother like me can feel.

256
00:15:26,383 --> 00:15:29,678
After everything you said
it's just "vibes"?

257
00:15:30,554 --> 00:15:32,723
I'm Team Sofie!

258
00:15:33,557 --> 00:15:34,558
Sofie.

259
00:15:37,561 --> 00:15:38,687
Guys.

260
00:15:38,771 --> 00:15:41,357
I'm so sticky!

261
00:15:41,857 --> 00:15:44,234
Still no water?

262
00:15:45,486 --> 00:15:49,698
My brain is getting fried looking
for La Morte Bianca.

263
00:15:49,782 --> 00:15:54,662
I feel like I want to drink
the water dripping from the AC.

264
00:16:00,292 --> 00:16:01,585
Hello Agent Dara.

265
00:16:01,669 --> 00:16:02,920
When will there be water?

266
00:16:05,130 --> 00:16:06,757
Since the safe house
is in a remote location,

267
00:16:06,840 --> 00:16:09,510
you'll probably get
your water ration tomorrow.

268
00:16:10,094 --> 00:16:13,430
<i>They prioritize areas that are closer.</i>

269
00:16:13,514 --> 00:16:15,265
So by that time,

270
00:16:15,349 --> 00:16:16,892
you might finally get water.

271
00:16:16,976 --> 00:16:19,645
So there's no point
sending them there tomorrow.

272
00:16:19,728 --> 00:16:22,189
Wait, what happened?
Why is there no water supply?

273
00:16:22,272 --> 00:16:24,775
A water pipeline was damaged.

274
00:16:24,858 --> 00:16:29,279
They said water might come back
tonight, around 9 p.m.

275
00:16:29,863 --> 00:16:31,198
Is there any other way?

276
00:16:36,620 --> 00:16:39,206
There's a hand pump near the safe house,

277
00:16:39,289 --> 00:16:42,126
around 700 meters away.

278
00:16:42,209 --> 00:16:43,585
Can you walk that far?

279
00:16:44,378 --> 00:16:46,130
I don't have a choice.

280
00:16:46,714 --> 00:16:48,340
Okay, bye.

281
00:16:50,801 --> 00:16:52,261
We need to fetch water.

282
00:16:52,344 --> 00:16:53,804
Mikoy, come with me.

283
00:16:53,887 --> 00:16:55,931
Okay, I'll come with you and Chiara.

284
00:17:02,146 --> 00:17:05,065
I'll just stay here, I'm too sticky.

285
00:17:05,149 --> 00:17:07,192
You two go with Agent Alex.

286
00:17:07,776 --> 00:17:13,032
After all,
you're just going to fetch water, right?

287
00:17:17,828 --> 00:17:19,288
If Chiara stays here,

288
00:17:19,872 --> 00:17:21,623
Cocoy needs to stay here too.

289
00:17:25,919 --> 00:17:27,838
- Let's go, Mikoy.
- Okay.

290
00:17:27,921 --> 00:17:30,215
- Hurry up, sweetheart.
- Take care, you two.

291
00:17:37,473 --> 00:17:38,766
All right.

292
00:17:40,225 --> 00:17:41,268
This is hot.

293
00:17:54,239 --> 00:17:56,658
What is it? Do you want to say something?

294
00:17:58,327 --> 00:18:00,287
My favorite color is blue, what about you?

295
00:18:01,455 --> 00:18:02,498
What?

296
00:18:02,581 --> 00:18:03,999
Where did that come from?

297
00:18:05,626 --> 00:18:06,835
I like pink.

298
00:18:08,337 --> 00:18:09,838
Mine depends on my mood.

299
00:18:09,922 --> 00:18:11,340
But today, red.

300
00:18:14,968 --> 00:18:16,470
I like yellow.

301
00:18:18,430 --> 00:18:20,808
Sunshine yellow or mustard yellow?

302
00:18:25,145 --> 00:18:25,979
Okay.

303
00:18:28,065 --> 00:18:29,108
What's your favorite dish?

304
00:18:31,485 --> 00:18:32,694
Pork sinigang ribs,

305
00:18:32,778 --> 00:18:34,029
- With taro.
- With taro!

306
00:18:34,113 --> 00:18:35,280
Morning would work too!

307
00:18:41,161 --> 00:18:42,496
For men?

308
00:18:42,579 --> 00:18:43,831
What do you like?

309
00:18:47,709 --> 00:18:51,797
I like someone a bit tall.

310
00:18:52,381 --> 00:18:55,092
But not too short either.

311
00:18:55,676 --> 00:18:56,969
Personality?

312
00:19:00,097 --> 00:19:01,056
Simple.

313
00:19:01,140 --> 00:19:02,599
Kind-hearted.

314
00:19:03,475 --> 00:19:04,643
And also,

315
00:19:04,726 --> 00:19:05,894
down to earth.

316
00:19:06,645 --> 00:19:08,147
So you like earthworms?

317
00:19:08,230 --> 00:19:09,857
Just stand it up and it's fine.

318
00:19:09,940 --> 00:19:11,150
Perfect height.

319
00:19:11,233 --> 00:19:12,609
And living down to earth.

320
00:19:13,193 --> 00:19:14,153
Right?

321
00:19:14,820 --> 00:19:15,654
Exactly, Bechay!

322
00:19:15,737 --> 00:19:17,239
- You're so good, you're so good!
- Oh, you…

323
00:19:17,322 --> 00:19:21,785
Because, you know, he really does
look like a checkered earthworm,

324
00:19:21,869 --> 00:19:22,911
just smarter.

325
00:19:23,412 --> 00:19:26,290
Wait, what are you guys
even talking about?

326
00:19:26,790 --> 00:19:28,834
Just Sofie's favorites.

327
00:19:30,502 --> 00:19:31,920
Wait, it's almost done.

328
00:19:32,421 --> 00:19:34,339
Movie? What's your favorite movie?

329
00:19:35,215 --> 00:19:36,675
Wait, wait, wait.

330
00:19:37,176 --> 00:19:39,052
I know what you're doing.

331
00:19:39,970 --> 00:19:42,014
This is slambook questions, right?

332
00:19:43,140 --> 00:19:44,266
Yes.

333
00:19:44,349 --> 00:19:45,893
I saw it on the internet.

334
00:19:49,521 --> 00:19:50,606
For whom?

335
00:19:51,523 --> 00:19:55,068
For you or for someone else?

336
00:19:56,695 --> 00:19:57,905
So full of herself!

337
00:20:17,424 --> 00:20:19,927
Hey Mikoy, you're wasting water.

338
00:20:20,010 --> 00:20:21,261
Sorry.

339
00:20:21,345 --> 00:20:23,805
Feels like military training, huh?
Isn't this how it is?

340
00:20:25,182 --> 00:20:26,975
Look at that, you spilled it.

341
00:20:27,684 --> 00:20:28,602
Come on.

342
00:20:30,520 --> 00:20:32,272
I'm cutting your water ration.

343
00:20:32,356 --> 00:20:34,858
How dare you! Take that back.

344
00:20:35,442 --> 00:20:36,652
No, final decision.

345
00:20:36,735 --> 00:20:38,278
Final?

346
00:20:38,362 --> 00:20:39,446
Really final?

347
00:20:43,325 --> 00:20:45,327
- You're playing now?
- Is that the final?

348
00:20:46,745 --> 00:20:47,871
- What?
- Enough.

349
00:20:48,789 --> 00:20:51,333
- All right, so?
- Oh, you're attacking too.

350
00:20:52,251 --> 00:20:53,418
Hey!

351
00:20:53,502 --> 00:20:55,504
Are you seriously
going to play with water?

352
00:20:58,882 --> 00:21:01,385
Hey! Mikoy, stop it.

353
00:21:02,177 --> 00:21:03,595
Seriously, seriously.

354
00:21:03,679 --> 00:21:05,973
- Okay I will use this-
- Go on, try it.

355
00:21:06,056 --> 00:21:07,599
- Go ahead.
- Okay, stop it, stop it.

356
00:21:07,683 --> 00:21:09,226
- Go on.
- Don't waste water like that.

357
00:21:09,309 --> 00:21:10,602
Wasting?

358
00:21:10,686 --> 00:21:12,145
Yes, it's so far away!

359
00:21:12,229 --> 00:21:13,939
Look, I'm carrying two, you just have one.

360
00:21:14,022 --> 00:21:15,941
Of course, I'm a girl, what do you expect?

361
00:21:16,024 --> 00:21:17,359
Fine! Wait.

362
00:21:17,442 --> 00:21:19,236
- Enough, stop it.
- What is this?

363
00:21:19,861 --> 00:21:22,114
It's like… it's raining a bit.

364
00:21:22,197 --> 00:21:24,116
- Mikoy, what.
- It's drizzling?

365
00:21:24,199 --> 00:21:26,201
- So annoying.
- It's raining!

366
00:21:26,285 --> 00:21:28,328
Hey, what is it?

367
00:21:28,412 --> 00:21:29,788
You're so annoying.

368
00:21:30,789 --> 00:21:32,791
- Really?
- Oh, you want it?

369
00:21:32,874 --> 00:21:34,710
- No, I'm just saying.
- Fine.

370
00:21:39,464 --> 00:21:42,759
Want some jelly beans?
I found some in the pantry, want some?

371
00:21:49,266 --> 00:21:50,309
Okay, what a shame.

372
00:21:52,894 --> 00:21:54,938
Guys! We've got jelly!

373
00:21:56,315 --> 00:21:57,399
Hey, I want some!

374
00:22:00,193 --> 00:22:03,655
This jelly is so good! So jelly!

375
00:22:04,781 --> 00:22:07,117
Wakes you up! So jelly!

376
00:22:11,455 --> 00:22:14,624
If you were really listening
to my answers earlier.

377
00:22:16,251 --> 00:22:17,502
What's my favorite dish?

378
00:22:17,586 --> 00:22:19,046
That's it?

379
00:22:19,880 --> 00:22:22,549
Pork sinigang ribs, with taro.

380
00:22:22,632 --> 00:22:24,051
Even in the morning.

381
00:22:26,219 --> 00:22:28,680
Nice, nice, nice, okay, okay.

382
00:22:29,306 --> 00:22:30,348
Here.

383
00:22:30,849 --> 00:22:32,267
What's my favorite color?

384
00:22:32,893 --> 00:22:33,894
Yellow!

385
00:22:34,394 --> 00:22:36,063
And not just any yellow,

386
00:22:36,563 --> 00:22:38,106
sunflower yellow.

387
00:22:38,190 --> 00:22:39,399
See?

388
00:22:39,483 --> 00:22:40,400
Nice!

389
00:22:40,901 --> 00:22:41,902
Here, here.

390
00:22:42,611 --> 00:22:43,987
What's my favorite flower?

391
00:22:45,280 --> 00:22:46,907
I didn't even ask that!

392
00:22:46,990 --> 00:22:48,700
You're not listening.

393
00:22:48,784 --> 00:22:50,243
But that's easy.

394
00:22:50,327 --> 00:22:51,411
What?

395
00:22:51,495 --> 00:22:52,662
Sunflower!

396
00:22:54,247 --> 00:22:56,249
You got it right!

397
00:22:56,875 --> 00:22:58,919
But I feel like you won't get this one.

398
00:22:59,002 --> 00:22:59,878
Yes.

399
00:23:00,587 --> 00:23:01,797
What's my favorite song?

400
00:23:01,880 --> 00:23:02,964
The one you always sing.

401
00:23:03,048 --> 00:23:04,091
What?

402
00:23:09,638 --> 00:23:10,514
There.

403
00:23:10,597 --> 00:23:11,723
In love, huh.

404
00:23:15,519 --> 00:23:16,686
So you're in love.

405
00:23:24,444 --> 00:23:25,445
Is this the house?

406
00:23:25,529 --> 00:23:27,280
Yes it seems like this is it.

407
00:23:28,156 --> 00:23:29,157
Oh, there's someone.

408
00:23:29,241 --> 00:23:30,200
Sir.

409
00:23:30,826 --> 00:23:31,993
Are you from here?

410
00:23:32,994 --> 00:23:34,121
Why?

411
00:23:34,204 --> 00:23:35,997
We're just here to do a census.

412
00:23:36,081 --> 00:23:37,874
Do you live in this house?

413
00:23:37,958 --> 00:23:41,378
Census? Isn't that every five years?

414
00:23:41,461 --> 00:23:43,463
We already had a census last year.

415
00:23:48,009 --> 00:23:49,928
- Let's go, let's go.
- You're new here.

416
00:24:00,063 --> 00:24:02,315
You know that's dehydrating, but okay!

417
00:24:05,485 --> 00:24:06,862
- Okay.
- Later.

418
00:24:06,945 --> 00:24:08,446
- You go ahead.
- Okay.

419
00:24:09,781 --> 00:24:10,782
Okay.

420
00:24:14,202 --> 00:24:16,830
Welcome to the criminal TED Talk.

421
00:24:19,666 --> 00:24:20,667
So here's what happened,

422
00:24:20,750 --> 00:24:21,877
I checked their crypto,

423
00:24:21,960 --> 00:24:24,504
one source only,
but all their money was there.

424
00:24:24,588 --> 00:24:26,882
It was sent to
a Taytay residence, very secured.

425
00:24:26,965 --> 00:24:29,176
The're so many- Lots of guards.

426
00:24:29,259 --> 00:24:32,345
But I got it with my app.
So there. Do you understand?

427
00:24:36,850 --> 00:24:38,185
Anyway,

428
00:24:40,103 --> 00:24:41,980
at this point, we still don't know

429
00:24:42,063 --> 00:24:44,316
why La Morte Bianca is building a site.

430
00:24:44,399 --> 00:24:45,442
That's it!

431
00:24:45,525 --> 00:24:47,235
- Yes.
- Got it!

432
00:24:47,319 --> 00:24:49,404
- Nice!
- Not confirmed yet.

433
00:24:50,363 --> 00:24:51,281
Well.

434
00:24:52,991 --> 00:24:56,578
Or if you really want to know,
what they know,

435
00:24:57,996 --> 00:25:01,082
we need to talk to one of their people.

436
00:26:18,785 --> 00:26:21,037
Mikoy in our line of work,
it's hard to trust someone.

437
00:26:21,121 --> 00:26:23,999
Because if we fail, there are people
that will be hurt and endangered.

438
00:26:25,083 --> 00:26:27,168
I won't promise
that I will give her my trust.

439
00:26:28,044 --> 00:26:29,421
But I will try to.

440
00:26:31,172 --> 00:26:32,424
Thank you.

441
00:26:48,064 --> 00:26:49,524
Sir, we have a proposal.

442
00:26:50,483 --> 00:26:52,819
<i>Chiara wants to reconnect</i>
<i>with Viktor Valtrovi</i>

443
00:26:52,902 --> 00:26:54,529
- to get information-
- No!
